This workout can be done outdoor, in your yard or at home on a sofa/ bed/ chair. 
15-20 reps each exercise / 3 sets each round. 45 seconds break between sets. At the end - plank till failure💪🏼 Outfit @stronger 
#fullbodyworkout #workoutmotivation #workoutroutine #lifestyleblogger #fitnessmotivation #londonlife

node.text:
I have finally filmed a workout video for you!! I know I promised to make this post a long time ago. Just so you know, I am not qualified as a fitness trainer. These are the exercises that I do and work the best for me. Some of them I've learnt from my personal trainer and others I've learnt from fitness bloggers.🏋🏽‍♀️ I prefer to do my workouts with small weights in order to keep the muscles toned, but not too big.
I repeat each exercise 20 times (each leg) in 3 rounds.💪🏼
❗️Very important❗️Never forget to warm up before starting your workout❗️
Hope this post was useful! Let me know in comments below if you want more videos like this!

node.text:
During summer I prefer to wear a more natural makeup. I want to let my skin breathe and give it a glowing, healthy look, that's why I use just a hydrating cream and tinted moisturiser to cover the imperfections.❤️
Products I've used in this video:

1. Isis Pharma Ruboril (great for those who suffer from Rosacea)
2. Creamy eye treatment with avocado from Kiehl's
3. Extra Illuminating Moisture Balm (Pink Glow) from Bobbi Brown
4. Bobbi Brown Nude finish Tinted Moisturizer SPF 15 
5. NARS Concealer
6. Terracotta Bronzing Powder from Guerlain
7. Dior Backstage Eyeshadow Pallete (Cool neutrals)
8. Artdeco Eyeliner 
9. Highlighter Becca (Parisian Lights)
10. Anastasia Beverly Hills Brow Definer 
11. Billion Dollar Brows transparent gel
12. L'oreal Telescopic mascara 
13. Maybelline lip liner (Nude Whisper)
14. Dior Lip Glow Balm

4. Vegan vanilla protein powder
5. Coconut milk
6. Blend
7. Add toppings 
Enjoy!! 🤗

node.text:
I found a portal to heaven!🤍 

This little baby akita dog was definitely the star of our trip! It was our present for the owner of this magical place! I'm so proud I came up with the name Agartha for her! The name is after a legendary world located at the core of Earth that I am passionate about! And the owner loved it so much!! If it were a boy we would name him Telos.
She really gave more life to this place and we are so glad to see how happy Agartha is in her new home!🐶
